    <briefdescription>
<para>DMA port interface — implement these for your platform. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Provides a portable DMA abstraction for memory-to-peripheral, peripheral-to-memory, and memory-to-memory transfers. The completion callback fires from ISR context — use <ref refid="syn__workqueue_8c_1aa21f36ebf0f10cc13bd62e2a55d34264" kindref="member">syn_workqueue_post()</ref> to defer heavy processing to the main context.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">void</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>on_dma_done(uint8_t<sp/><ref refid="syn__sha256_8c_1a040629ce734f8c5b8c1b917ee7330a7b" kindref="member">ch</ref>,<sp/><ref refid="syn__defs_8h_1ac74d19fd322a889de9e46b79fb277c00" kindref="member">SYN_Status</ref><sp/>result,<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">void</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>*ctx)<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Transfer<sp/>complete<sp/>—<sp/>process<sp/>data<sp/>or<sp/>post<sp/>to<sp/>workqueue</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
